# Copy to `immich.env` (same directory) and fill in before running the optional
# playbook bootstrap/99_optional_immich_db_backup.yaml. `immich.env` is gitignored;
# never commit the real file.
#
# This holds an Immich ADMIN API key, used ONLY to turn on Immich's built-in
# periodic database backup via the API (a one-time, non-destructive config change
# that leaves the Settings UI editable). It is not used at runtime by any service.
#
# Create the key in the Immich web UI as the OWNER/admin account:
#   Account Settings -> API Keys -> New API Key
# Grant it permission to read and update the system config (the simplest choice is
# "Select All" / all permissions; the minimum is systemConfig.read + systemConfig.update).
IMMICH_API_KEY=
